dct_title_s: LiDAR Breakline Rivers Milwaukee County, Wisconsin 2010
dct_description_sm: This line data layer represents the LiDAR breakline rivers for Milwaukee County, Wisconsin between April 16-18, 2010. The dataset was originally published by the Milwaukee County Land Information Office and Pictometry International Corporation (now part of EagleView) in 2010. For official metadata please see MilwaukeeCountyLiDARMetadata.htm in the Metadata folder.[Lidar Data Products for the Milwaukee, WI collection area. ESRI Multipoints and Terrain for the Bare Earth lidar points, Hydro and Transportation Breaklines, 5ft DEM, 1ft Contours tiled to manage file size, Voids >= 10 sq meters, Percent Slope, Degree Slope, 5ft Digital Surface Model (DSM), 5ft nDSM (Height Above Ground raster), Tiled Intensity Rasters.][The dataset consists of LiDAR data collection performed over Milwaukee County, WI April 16-18 2010. Products generated include a DEM, DSM, Voids, Slopes, Intensity Grids, Hydro Enforced Breaklines, Transportation Breaklines and 1ft Contours.]
